    "body":  "# MRL Increment 2 – InMemoryQualificationRequirementService (Read-Only)\n\n## Objective\nCreate a simple, read-only in-memory service to expose MRL entries for use in downstream development (UI prototyping, future assessments, etc).\n\nIn this context, MRL entries are represented by the `QualificationRequirement` domain entity introduced in Increment 1.\n\nThis service is non-persistent, non-editable, and meant only for internal use during prototyping.\n\n## Scope\n- ✅ In-memory service class (no database, no file I/O)\n- ✅ Fetch all requirements\n- ✅ Fetch by ID (Guid)\n- ✅ Filter by approval status (`RequirementApprovalStatus`)\n- ✅ Unit tests (lightweight)\n\n## Out of Scope\n- ❌ Persistence (e.g., Entity Framework, database access)\n- ❌ Write/update methods\n- ❌ Assessment logic (matching evidence to requirements)\n- ❌ Role mapping or assignment\n- ❌ UI logic\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### Class: `InMemoryQualificationRequirementService`\nA temporary, read-only store for `QualificationRequirement` entities.\n\n#### Required Methods\n```csharp\nList\u003cQualificationRequirement\u003e GetAll()\nQualificationRequirement? GetById(Guid id)\nList\u003cQualificationRequirement\u003e GetByApprovalStatus(RequirementApprovalStatus status)\n```\n\n### Test Coverage\nAdd a test class to validate expected behavior:\n\n- Can fetch all entries\n- Can fetch by known ID\n- Can return empty result for unknown ID\n- Can filter by `RequirementApprovalStatus`\n- Service does not mutate or persist state (read-only behavior)\n\nUse sample data (3–5 requirements with varied statuses and types).\n\n## Outcome\nA testable, read-only in-memory service that exposes the current MRL entries (`QualificationRequirement` instances), enabling UI integration via simple list and filter queries, without introducing UI components in this increment.\n\n## Notes\nThis will be replaced in a later increment by a persistent repository or API service.",
